<p><strong>Tip</strong>: One thing to pay attention to is that you must pass the same <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">history</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">dataProvider</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">authProvider</code> to both the redux Store creator and the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;Admin&gt;</code> component. But you donâ€™t need to pass the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">i18nProvider</code>.</p>

<h2 id="not-using-the-admin-components">Not Using the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;Admin&gt;</code> Components</h2>

<p>The <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;Admin&gt;</code> component takes care of defining the store (unless you provide one, as seen above), of setting the Translation and Authentication contexts, and of bootstrapping the Router. In case you need to override any of these, you can use your own component instead of <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;Admin&gt;</code>.</p>

<p>Here is the main code for bootstrapping a barebone react-admin application without <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;Admin&gt;</code>:</p>

<div class="language-diff highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="err">//</span> in src/App.js
